
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to replace a substring within a node's value using the [strings.replace] slot. It first sets the value of the [.result] node by replacing occurrences of a specific substring (defined by [[type]]) with a value retrieved from the [.arguments] node. The process involves using [set-value] to assign the modified string back to [.result].
 * 
 * 1. [set-value] - Sets the value of the [.result] node.
 * 2. [strings.replace] - Replaces occurrences of a substring within the [.result] node.
 * 3. [.] - Specifies the substring to be replaced, [[type]] in this case.
 * 4. [get-value] - Retrieves the replacement value from the [.arguments/*/type] node.
 */
set-value:x:@.result
   strings.replace:x:@.result
      .:[[type]]
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/type
